-- | Lifting functions into the "Elem domain"
-- Use this class to translate f :: a -> b into the corresponding (Elem -> Elem) function
class LiftElem a b where
  liftEl' :: (a -> b) -> (Elem -> Elem)
  liftEl  :: (a -> b) -> ([Elem] -> Elem)
  liftEl f (x:xs) = (liftEl' f) x
  liftEl f [] = Nil

-- | Lifting functions into the "Elem domain"
-- Use this class to translate f :: a1 -> a2 -> b into the corresponding (Elem -> Elem -> Elem) function
class LiftElem2 a1 a2 b where
  liftEl2' :: (a1 -> a2 -> b) -> (Elem -> Elem -> Elem)
  liftEl2  :: (a1 -> a2 -> b) -> ([Elem] -> Elem)
  liftEl2 f (x:y:xs) = (liftEl2' f) x y
  liftEl2 f (x:[])   = Nil
  liftEl2 f []       = Nil


-- | Lifting functions into the "Elem domain"
-- Use this class to translate f :: a1 -> a2 -> a3 -> b into the corresponding (Elem -> Elem -> Elem -> Elem) function
class LiftElem3 a1 a2 a3 b where
  liftEl3' :: (a1 -> a2 -> a3 -> b) -> (Elem -> Elem -> Elem -> Elem)
  liftEl3  :: (a1 -> a2 -> a3 -> b) -> ([Elem] -> Elem)
  liftEl3 f (x:y:z:xs) = (liftEl3' f) x y z
  liftEl3 f (x:y:[])   = Nil
  liftEl3 f (x:[])     = Nil
  liftEl3 f []         = Nil

-- =====================
-- == Generation of boiler plate code
-- =====================

{-
-- Two boilerplate styles --
-- Style1) straightforward:
instance LiftElem Bool Char    where liftEl' f (B x)  = C (f x);  liftEl' f _ = Nil
instance LiftElem Bool String  where liftEl' f (B x)  = S (f x);  liftEl' f _ = Nil

instance LiftElem Bool Int     where liftEl' f (B x)  = I (f x);  liftEl' f _ = Nil
instance LiftElem Bool Integer where liftEl' f (B x)  = J (f x);  liftEl' f _ = Nil

-- Style2) using toElem (reduces the boilerplate by a factor 10)
-- unary:
instance Elementable a => LiftElem Bool a    where liftEl' f (B x)  = toElem (f x);  liftEl' f _ = Nil
-- binary:
instance Elementable a => LiftElem2 Bool Bool a where liftEl2' f (B x) (B y) = toElem (f x y);  liftEl2' f _ _ = Nil
-}

genStrTy = ["Bool", "Char", "String", "Int", "Integer", "Double", "Day", "UTCTime", "ByteString", "Relvar"]
genStrEl = ["B", "C", "S", "I", "J", "D", "DD", "DT", "BS", "R"]
genTypeMap = Map.fromList $ zip genStrTy genStrEl


-- boilerplate functions, style 1
-- unary functions
genLiftElem11 :: (String, String) -> String
genLiftElem11 (strTy1,strTy) = "instance LiftElem " ++ strTy1 ++ " " ++ strTy ++ "        where liftEl' f (" ++ Map.findWithDefault "Z" strTy1 genTypeMap ++ " x)  = " ++ Map.findWithDefault "Z" strTy genTypeMap ++ " (f x);  liftEl' f _ = Nil"

-- binary functions
genLiftElem12 :: (String, String, String) -> String
genLiftElem12 (strTy1,strTy2,strTy) = "instance LiftElem2 " ++ strTy1 ++ " " ++ strTy2 ++ " " ++ strTy ++ "       where liftEl2' f (" ++ Map.findWithDefault "Z" strTy1 genTypeMap ++ " x) (" ++ Map.findWithDefault "Z" strTy2 genTypeMap ++ " y) = " ++ Map.findWithDefault "Z" strTy genTypeMap ++ " (f x y);  liftEl2' f _ _ = Nil"

-- boilercode generation for unary function (run genBoilerCode11)
genBoilerCode11 :: IO()
genBoilerCode11 = do
    let pairs = [(x,y) | x <- genStrTy, y <- genStrTy]
    putStrLn "-- == START : Code generated by genBoilCode =="
    mapM_ putStrLn $ map genLiftElem11 pairs
    putStrLn "-- == END : Code generated by genBoilCode =="

-- boilercode generation for binary function (run genBoilerCode12)
genBoilerCode12 :: IO()
genBoilerCode12 = do
    let triplets = [(x,y,z) | x <- genStrTy, y <- genStrTy, z <- genStrTy]
        xs = ["-- == START : Code generated by genBoilCode2 =="] ++ map genLiftElem12 triplets ++ ["-- == END : Code generated by genBoilCode2 =="]
    writeFile "./boilerplate2.txt" (unlines xs)


-- boilerplate functions, style 2
-- unary functions

genLiftElem21 strTy1 = "instance Elementable a => LiftElem " ++ strTy1 ++ " a where liftEl' f (" ++ Map.findWithDefault "Z" strTy1 genTypeMap ++ " x)  = toElem (f x);  liftEl' f _ = Nil"

-- binary functions
genLiftElem22 :: (String, String) -> String
genLiftElem22 (strTy1,strTy2) = "instance Elementable a => LiftElem2 " ++ strTy1 ++ " " ++ strTy2 ++ " a where liftEl2' f (" ++ Map.findWithDefault "Z" strTy1 genTypeMap ++ " x) (" ++ Map.findWithDefault "Z" strTy2 genTypeMap ++ " y) = toElem (f x y);  liftEl2' f _ _ = Nil"

    -- let pairs = [(x,y) | x <- genStrTy, y <- genStrTy]
    putStrLn "-- == START : Code generated by genBoilCode =="
    mapM_ putStrLn $ map genLiftElem21 genStrTy

        xs = ["-- == START : Code generated by genBoilCode2 =="] ++ map genLiftElem22 pairs ++ ["-- == END : Code generated by genBoilCode2 =="]
    mapM_ putStrLn xs
    -- writeFile "./boilerplate2.txt" (unlines xs) -- use if need to write to file
